messages.messageBody:
--- In AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com, Joyce Fetteroll <jfetteroll@...> wrote:
> There isn't a huge amount there but you can add your own if you live
> near something made famous :-)
>

If you add a spot, it doesn't automatically go on the map. They let you know that they will look at your information and contact you to tell you if they select it.

How could they not select my spot? The hotel where they filmed The Shining!

messages.messageBody:
Cool site.

I had a problem navigating it though. The "all spots" page, lists about 8
spots and then I couldn't get it to access anymore. Clicking on the yellow
tabs on the country didn't work either. Were you able to navigate that page?

Thanks,
Jacki
-----Original Message-----
From: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
[mailto:AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com]On Behalf Of Joyce Fetteroll
Sent: Friday, May 29, 2009 4:35 AM
To: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [AlwaysLearning] Where it's at





This was tacked by AOL onto the the bottom of someone email. People
locate places in songs and movies and TV shows on a map, with
pictures and descriptions.

http://www.whereitsat.com/

Things like:

The Office pizzaria
The Spider-Man diner -- that is now in Wyoming!
Alice's Restaurant in Stockbridge MA
Shawshank Redeption prison
Newhart Inn

There isn't a huge amount there but you can add your own if you live
near something made famous :-)

Joyce
